     <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start"><div class="max-w-3xl flex-1"><p class="text-sm font-medium text-accent mb-4">Rehabilitation Act of 1973</p><h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-zinc-900 leading-tight tracking-tight">ADHD and Section 504</h1><p class="mt-6 text-lg text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">Section 504 is the most common pathway for students with ADHD to receive school accommodations. Here is how it works, who qualifies, and what to expect from the process.</p></div><div class="hidden md:block w-80 flex-shrink-0"><img src="/images/section-504.webp" alt="Student studying with laptop for Section 504 accommodations" class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full" width="320" height="213" loading="eager" /></div></div>
